Japanese Sold Net 1174.8 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   T h e r e s a   B a r r a c l o u g h
-- 
2011-04-06T23:54:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/japanese-sold-net-1174-8-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
sellers of foreign bonds during the week ended April 1 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors sold 1174.8 billion yen ($13.8 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 23.8 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 33.9 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net sale of 1232.6 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 109.3 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 144.7 billion yen in stocks, and bought 460 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 714
billion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theresa Barraclough in Tokyo at   tbarraclough@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  